<p class='note'><strong>Note</strong>: Installing the BOSH CLI requires Ruby 1.9.3, 2.0.x, or 2.1.x.</p>

BOSH Command Line Interface (CLI) is used to interact with MicroBOSH and BOSH. To install BOSH CLI with the MicroBOSH plugin:

```
gem install bosh_cli bosh_cli_plugin_micro
```

Use the following command to consult the BOSH CLI help:

```
bosh help --all
```

## Pre-requisites on Ubuntu Trusty

Install pre-requisites on Ubuntu Trusty before running `gem install` commands:

```
sudo apt-get install build-essential ruby ruby-dev libxml2-dev libsqlite3-dev libxslt1-dev libpq-dev libmysqlclient-dev
```

